cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DS 

The paper deals with the spread of malware in mobile networks and proposes a containment strategy based on temporal complex network metrics. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of Computer Security (cs.CR), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). However, given the focus on malware propagation and containment, cs.CR is the most likely category, followed by cs.SI and cs.NI.
